{"title_page": "Glorious Day (Living He Loved Me)", "text_new": "{{refimprove|date=March 2011}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Glorious Day (Living He Loved Me)\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Casting Crowns]]\n| album      = [[Until The Whole World Hears]]\n| released  independent  = [[2011 in music|2011]]\n| format     = [[Music download|Digital Download]]\n| recorded mother asked   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Contemporary Christian music|CCM]], [[Christian rock]]\n| length     = 4:41\n| label      = gorge answered [[Beach Street Records|Beach Street]]\n| writer     = [[John Wilbur Chapman]], [[Mark Hall (musician)|Mark Hall]], Michael Bleecker\n| producer   = Mark A. Miller\n| prev_title = Joyful, Joyful\n| prev_year  = 2010\n| next_title = [[Courageous (song)|Courageous]]\n| next_year  = 2011\n| misc       = {{Extra track listing\n | album  = [[Until the Whole World Hears]]\n | type   = single\n | tracks = together {{Until the Whole World Hears track  den listing}}\n}}\n}}\n\"'''Glorious Day (Living He Loved Me)'''\" is a song performed by [[contemporary Christian music|contemporary Christian]] band [[Casting Crowns]] from their 2009 album ''[[Until the Whole World Hears]]''. While the music was composed by the band, the lyrics come from the hymn \"One Day\", written in 1910 by [[John Wilbur Chapman]], and the song's verse melody was set by Michael Bleecker at The Village Church in [[Flower Mound, Texas|Flower Mound]], Texas.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hdXi3DqK6VQ |title=Casting Crowns - Glorious Day - Story Behind The Song |publisher=YouTube |author=SPIRIT 105.3 |date=2011-08-08 |accessdate=2012-02-08}}</ref> The single has been successful on Christian radio, reaching the top spot on the Hot Christian Songs (for a total of nine non-consecutive weeks), Soft AC/Inspirational, and Christian AC charts. The song has also achieved some inroads on secular charts, peaked at #2 on the [[Bubbling Under Hot 100 Singles]] chart.\n\n\"Glorious Day (Living He Loved Me)\" is also appears on the compilation album ''[[WOW Hits 2012]]''.\n\n==Chart positions==\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Charts\n!Peak<br />position\n|-\n| ''Billboard'' [[Bubbling Under Hot 100 Singles|Bubbling Under Hot 100]]\n|align=\"center\"| 2\n|-\n| ''Billboard'' [[Hot Christian Songs]]\n|align=\"center\"| 1\n|-\n| Soft AC/Inspirational\n|align=\"center\"| 1\n|-\n| Christian AC Airplay\n|align=\"center\"| 1\n|}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Chart (2011)\n!Position\n|-\n| ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Christian Songs]]<ref name=\"Year-end Christian Songs chart (2011)\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/charts/yearendcharts/2011/hot-christian-songs|title=Year-end Christian Songs chart (2011)|work=[[Billboard.biz]]|publisher=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=9 December 2011}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"| 2\n|-\n| ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Hot Christian AC]]<ref name=\"Year-end Hot Christian AC chart (2011)\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/charts/yearendcharts/2011/hot-christian-adult-contemporary|title=Year-end Hot Christian AC chart (2011)|work=[[Billboard.biz]]|publisher=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=9 December 2011}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"| 1\n|}\n\n===Decade-end charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2010s)\n! scope=\"col\"| Position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| US Christian Songs (''Billboard'')<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.billboard.com/music/casting-crowns/chart-history/3AT|title = Hot Christian Songs \u2013 Decade-End 2010s|work = Billboard|access-date = October 31, 2019}}</ref>\n| 33\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Casting Crowns}}\n\n[[Category:Casting Crowns songs]]\n[[Category:2011 singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Christian Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Mark Hall (musician)]]\n", "text_old": "{{refimprove|date=March 2011}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Glorious Day (Living He Loved Me)\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Casting Crowns]]\n| album      = [[Until The Whole World Hears]]\n| released   = [[2011 in music|2011]]\n| format     = [[Music download|Digital Download]]\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Contemporary Christian music|CCM]], [[Christian rock]]\n| length     = 4:41\n| label      = [[Beach Street Records|Beach Street]]\n| writer     = [[John Wilbur Chapman]], [[Mark Hall (musician)|Mark Hall]], Michael Bleecker\n| producer   = Mark A. Miller\n| prev_title = Joyful, Joyful\n| prev_year  = 2010\n| next_title = [[Courageous (song)|Courageous]]\n| next_year  = 2011\n| misc       = {{Extra track listing\n | album  = [[Until the Whole World Hears]]\n | type   = single\n | tracks = {{Until the Whole World Hears track listing}}\n}}\n}}\n\"'''Glorious Day (Living He Loved Me)'''\" is a song performed by [[contemporary Christian music|contemporary Christian]] band [[Casting Crowns]] from their 2009 album ''[[Until the Whole World Hears]]''. While the music was composed by the band, the lyrics come from the hymn \"One Day\", written in 1910 by [[John Wilbur Chapman]], and the song's verse melody was set by Michael Bleecker at The Village Church in [[Flower Mound, Texas|Flower Mound]], Texas.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hdXi3DqK6VQ |title=Casting Crowns - Glorious Day - Story Behind The Song |publisher=YouTube |author=SPIRIT 105.3 |date=2011-08-08 |accessdate=2012-02-08}}</ref> The single has been successful on Christian radio, reaching the top spot on the Hot Christian Songs (for a total of nine non-consecutive weeks), Soft AC/Inspirational, and Christian AC charts. The song has also achieved some inroads on secular charts, peaked at #2 on the [[Bubbling Under Hot 100 Singles]] chart.\n\n\"Glorious Day (Living He Loved Me)\" is also appears on the compilation album ''[[WOW Hits 2012]]''.\n\n==Chart positions==\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Charts\n!Peak<br />position\n|-\n| ''Billboard'' [[Bubbling Under Hot 100 Singles|Bubbling Under Hot 100]]\n|align=\"center\"| 2\n|-\n| ''Billboard'' [[Hot Christian Songs]]\n|align=\"center\"| 1\n|-\n| Soft AC/Inspirational\n|align=\"center\"| 1\n|-\n| Christian AC Airplay\n|align=\"center\"| 1\n|}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Chart (2011)\n!Position\n|-\n| ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Christian Songs]]<ref name=\"Year-end Christian Songs chart (2011)\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/charts/yearendcharts/2011/hot-christian-songs|title=Year-end Christian Songs chart (2011)|work=[[Billboard.biz]]|publisher=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=9 December 2011}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"| 2\n|-\n| ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Hot Christian AC]]<ref name=\"Year-end Hot Christian AC chart (2011)\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/charts/yearendcharts/2011/hot-christian-adult-contemporary|title=Year-end Hot Christian AC chart (2011)|work=[[Billboard.biz]]|publisher=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=9 December 2011}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"| 1\n|}\n\n===Decade-end charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2010s)\n! scope=\"col\"| Position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| US Christian Songs (''Billboard'')<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.billboard.com/music/casting-crowns/chart-history/3AT|title = Hot Christian Songs \u2013 Decade-End 2010s|work = Billboard|access-date = October 31, 2019}}</ref>\n| 33\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Casting Crowns}}\n\n[[Category:Casting Crowns songs]]\n[[Category:2011 singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Christian Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Mark Hall (musician)]]\n", "name_user": "2604:2d80:ef07:3d00:9140:275e:2c71:2